cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with bidirectional neural sequence models and their application to image captioning, which involves both natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel task, which requires reasoning about both past and future sentence structure, indicating a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
